# Exercise 2: Implementing the Factory Method Pattern

## Objective
To understand and implement the Factory Method Design Pattern in Java.

## Description
The Factory Method Pattern is a creational design pattern that delegates object creation to a factory class. It allows the client code to create objects without directly instantiating concrete classes.

## Files Included

- Shape.java
- Circle.java
- Rectangle.java
- ShapeFactory.java
- FactoryPatternTest.java

## Sample Output

Drawing Circle
Drawing Rectangle

## Learning Outcomes

- Understanding Factory Method Pattern
- Interface-based programming
- Encapsulation of object creation
- Reduced coupling between client and implementation classes

## Conclusion

The Factory Method Pattern was successfully implemented. The factory class creates and returns the required object based on the input provided by the client.